==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Process plate
<hw>Proc"ess plate</hw>. <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A plate prepared by a
mechanical process, esp. a photomechanical process.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>A very slow photographic plate, giving good contrasts between high
lights and shadows, used esp. for making lantern slides.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proces verbal</ent>⟦br⟧
